basics.summary: I am studying for a B.S. in Computer Science in the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii. I expect to graduate in Spring, 2020.

work.summary: Worked on Kenya Health Information system products used in Nakuru and Baringo Counties.
highlights: Deployment of the extended KenyaEMR systems at facilities in Nakuru and Baringo counties.

Leading student engagement and facilitating the development of solutions for the Extended KenyaEMR, CPIMS, MOH Data analytic platform and the County annual workplan process in the Health Information systems.

volunteer.summary: This is a group for anyone interested in 'Vue.js - The Progressive JavaScript Framework'. The goal is to provide monthly meetups where people give talks on Vue.js and related topics, and people can get together with other developers in the community.

highlights: I hosted and organized events and workshops to increase students skills in areas of web development, mobile app development and action on Google.
I worked with local organizations to identify issues which could be resolved using mobile applications and get these applications developed by the students in their clubs.
I gained relevant industry experience by solving problems for local organization with technology based solutions.
I facilitated students prototyp showcase and solutions to their local community, university and industry leaders
I grew students knowledge on developer technologies and more through peer to peer workshops and events
